6.2 Upgrade Notes state: 
{quote}Note, you cannot upgrade from JIRA 4.3.x or earlier, directly to JIRA 6.2. You must upgrade to an interim version first. See Skipping Major Versions When Upgrading JIRA.
{quote}

but "Skipping Major Versions When Upgrading JIRA" states:
{quote}Upgrade to an interim version (JIRA 3.x or earlier only): Upgrade to JIRA 4.4.5 following these Upgrading JIRA with a Fallback Method instructions. 
{quote}

So to upgrade from 4.3.2, do I need to upgrade to an intermediate version or not? If so, to what version should the intermediate upgrade be?

