It appears that DefaultUserManager uses a hashmap to compare lower case usernames only under the condition that there are multiple user directories. 

The code:
{code}
    private Collection<User> getAllUsersFromCrowd()
...
       {
            // Use a map to remove duplicate usernames
            // We are looping in reverse order so that higher users push out shadowed users
            final Map<String, User> userMap = new HashMap<String, User>();
            for (Directory directory : activeDirectories)
            {
                for (User user : getAllUsersFromDirectory(directory, false))
                {
                    userMap.put(IdentifierUtils.toLowerCase(user.getName()), user);
                }
            }
            allUsers = userMap.values();
{code}

