In the changelog section of a webhook POST body, custom fields are identified by their name rather than their key. This is inconsistent with how non-custom fields are treated. For example here is a custom field:

"changelog"=>{"id"=>"14507", "items"=>[{"field"=>"Release notes", "fieldtype"=>"custom", "from"=>nil, "fromString"=>"Release this month!", "to"=>nil, "toString"=>"Release this month or next."}]}, "timestamp"=>1399311766637}

It seems to me that the "field" field should have contained "customfield_10300".

For built-in fields the key is used, e.g. 

"changelog"=>{"id"=>"14510", "items"=>[{"field"=>"summary", "fieldtype"=>"jira", "from"=>nil, "fromString"=>"Shovel the snow", "to"=>nil, "toString"=>"Shovel the snow now"}]}

Note the lower case "summary".

