There is no restriction for user to create *very* expensive gadgets and put them under a single dashboard. When there is multiple users accessing or refreshing the high profile dashboard repeatedly, it triggers CPU spike and JIRA to be very slow to the point it requires a restart.

At the moment, there is no way for the system admin to identify which filter/dashboard/gadgets consume resources. 

Ideally, JIRA should prevent this from happening, considering the system admin can not control the user behavior. At least, there should be a tool/report for system-admin to quickly identify the offending dashboard.

